%U A392559 882,918,960,966,1044,1050,1116,1128,1140,1188,1224,1260,1296,1368,1386,1404,1422
%N A392559 Numbers x such that for some y, a divisor of x such that 1<y<x, the following four numbers are prime: x*y+1, x*y-1, x/y+1, x/y-1.
%C A392559 All terms are multiples of 6.
%o A392559 (Python)
%o A392559 from sympy import isprime, divisors
%o A392559 print([x for x in range(2,2000) if any(all(isprime(v) for v in (x//y-1, x//y+1, x*y-1, x*y+1)) for y in divisors(x)[1:-1])])
%o A392559 (PARI) isok(k) = fordiv(k, d, if ((d>1) && (d<k) && isprime(k*d+1) && isprime(k*d-1) && isprime(k/d+1) && isprime(k/d-1), return(1))); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Mar 16 2026
%Y A392559 Cf. A000040.
%Y A392559 Subsequence of A280270 (both x/y+1 and x*y+1 are prime).
